  "prompt": "Which phone is best to buy under 17000 rs?",
  "response": "When considering a smartphone under 17000 INR, several excellent options offer a good balance of performance, camera quality, and battery life. Here are some top recommendations as of the latest updates:\n\n### 1. **Redmi Note 10 Pro**\n   - **Price**: Around \u20b916,000\n   - **Key Features**: \n     - **Display**: 6.67-inch Super AMOLED, 120Hz refresh rate\n     - **Processor**: Qualcomm Snapdragon 732G\n     - **Camera**: Quad-camera setup with 64MP primary sensor\n     - **Battery**: 5020mAh with 33W fast charging\n   - **Pros**: Excellent display, good performance, versatile camera setup, and long battery life.\n\n### 2. **Realme 8 Pro**\n   - **Price**: Around \u20b917,000\n   - **Key Features**:\n     - **Display**: 6.4-inch Super AMOLED\n     - **Processor**: Qualcomm Snapdragon 720G\n     - **Camera**: 108MP primary sensor in quad-camera setup\n     - **Battery**: 4500mAh with 50W fast charging\n   - **Pros**: High-resolution camera, fast charging, and a vibrant display.\n\n### 3. **Samsung Galaxy M32**\n   - **Price**: Around \u20b915,000\n   - **Key Features**:\n     - **Display**: 6.4-inch Super AMOLED\n     - **Processor**: MediaTek Helio G80\n     - **Camera**: 64MP primary sensor in quad-camera setup\n     - **Battery**: Massive 6000mAh with 25W fast charging\n   - **Pros**: Large battery, good camera, and reliable performance.\n\n### 4. **Motorola G60**\n   - **Price**: Around \u20b917,000\n   - **Key Features**:\n     - **Display**: 6.8-inch IPS LCD, 120Hz refresh rate\n     - **Processor**: Qualcomm Snapdragon 732G\n     - **Camera**: 108MP primary sensor in triple-camera setup\n     - **Battery**: 6000mAh with 30W fast charging\n   - **Pros**: Large display with high refresh rate, impressive battery life, and high-resolution camera.\n\n### 5. **Poco X3 Pro**\n   - **Price**: Around \u20b916,000\n   - **Key Features**:\n     - **Display**: 6.67-inch IPS LCD, 120Hz refresh rate\n     - **Processor**: Qualcomm Snapdragon 860\n     - **Camera**: 48MP primary sensor in quad-camera setup\n     - **Battery**: 5160mAh with 33W fast charging\n   - **Pros**: Powerful processor, smooth display, and good battery life.\n\nEach of these phones has its strengths, and the best choice depends on your priorities, such as camera quality, battery life, or processing power. I recommend checking the latest prices and offers as they can fluctuate and impact your final decision.",
